'''''A Treatise on the Law of the Prerogatives of the Crown''''' (full title: ''A Treatise on the Law of the Prerogatives of the Crown; and the Relative Duties and Rights of the Subject'') is an 1820 legal text by [[Joseph Chitty (the younger)|Joseph Chitty]]. The text provides the most comprehensive list of royal [[prerogative powers]] in the [[United Kingdom]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.parliament.uk/commons/lib/research/briefings/snpc-03861.pdf |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2010-04-20 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100423150250/http://www.parliament.uk/commons/lib/research/briefings/snpc-03861.pdf |archivedate=2010-04-23 |df= }}</ref>
